17/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos on Thursday (16 October) signed agreements with Serbia-Montenegro on building a highway between Belgrade and Athens and on providing aid for the maintenance of the power grid in southern Serbia and for hospitals in Montenegro. 
Athens is offering 238m euros in aid for the reconstruction of Serbia-Montenegro.
Also Thursday, Bulgaria and Bosnia and Herzegovina signed a free trade agreement, as well as an agreement that eases visa regulations for holders of official and diplomatic passports. 
(Trud, Dnevnik - 17/10/03; AFP, BNT, BTA, BNR - 16/10/03)
